apIpv4OspfMib.description: This MIB module describes the ArrowPoint enterprise MIB support for the Routing Information Protocol

apIpv4OspfRedistributeLocal.name: apIpv4OspfRedistributeLocal
apIpv4OspfRedistributeLocal.description: If enabled, local (direct) routes will be advertised by OSPF.

apIpv4OspfLocalType.name: apIpv4OspfLocalType
apIpv4OspfLocalType.description: If local routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the ASE type to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfLocalMetric.name: apIpv4OspfLocalMetric
apIpv4OspfLocalMetric.description: If local routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the metric to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfLocalTag.name: apIpv4OspfLocalTag
apIpv4OspfLocalTag.description: If local routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the tag value to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfRedistributeStatic.name: apIpv4OspfRedistributeStatic
apIpv4OspfRedistributeStatic.description: If enabled, static routes will be advertised by OSPF.

apIpv4OspfStaticType.name: apIpv4OspfStaticType
apIpv4OspfStaticType.description: If static routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the ASE type to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfStaticMetric.name: apIpv4OspfStaticMetric
apIpv4OspfStaticMetric.description: If static routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the metric to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfStaticTag.name: apIpv4OspfStaticTag
apIpv4OspfStaticTag.description: If static routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the tag value to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfRedistributeRip.name: apIpv4OspfRedistributeRip
apIpv4OspfRedistributeRip.description: If enabled, RIP routes will be advertised by OSPF.

apIpv4OspfRipType.name: apIpv4OspfRipType
apIpv4OspfRipType.description: If RIP routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the ASE type to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfRipMetric.name: apIpv4OspfRipMetric
apIpv4OspfRipMetric.description: If RIP routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the metric to use when advertising the routes. If zero is specified, the RIP metric will be used.

apIpv4OspfRipTag.name: apIpv4OspfRipTag
apIpv4OspfRipTag.description: If RIP routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the tag value to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfOriginateDefault.name: apIpv4OspfOriginateDefault
apIpv4OspfOriginateDefault.description: If enabled, an ASE will be generated for the default route.

apIpv4OspfDefaultType.name: apIpv4OspfDefaultType
apIpv4OspfDefaultType.description: If a default ASE is originated by OSPF, this is the ASE type to use when advertising the route.

apIpv4OspfDefaultMetric.name: apIpv4OspfDefaultMetric
apIpv4OspfDefaultMetric.description: If a default ASE is originated by OSPF, this is the metric to use when advertising the route.

apIpv4OspfDefaultTag.name: apIpv4OspfDefaultTag
apIpv4OspfDefaultTag.description: If a default ASE is originated by OSPF, this is the tag value to use when advertising the route.

apIpv4OspfRedistributeFirewall.name: apIpv4OspfRedistributeFirewall
apIpv4OspfRedistributeFirewall.description: If enabled, firewall routes will be advertised by OSPF.

apIpv4OspfFirewallType.name: apIpv4OspfFirewallType
apIpv4OspfFirewallType.description: If firewall routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the ASE type to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfFirewallMetric.name: apIpv4OspfFirewallMetric
apIpv4OspfFirewallMetric.description: If firewall routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the metric to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfFirewallTag.name: apIpv4OspfFirewallTag
apIpv4OspfFirewallTag.description: If firewall routes are advertised by OSPF, this is the tag value to use when advertising the routes.

apIpv4OspfAdvRouteStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.
